---
By: Zhuangzi
Source:
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Locus:
    Chapter: 6
    Paragraph: 10
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: The Great And Venerable Teacher
---
Therefore his liking was one and his not liking was one. His being one
was one and his not being one was one. In being one, he was acting as a
companion of Heaven. In not being one, he was acting as a companion of
man. When man and Heaven do not defeat each other, then we may be said
to have the True Man.
